.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-COMMENT 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 0.5.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-comment \- add a comment to an issue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue comment
.I <issue-id>
.B \-m
.I <message>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add a comment to an existing issue.
The comment is recorded as a new commit appended to the issue's
commit chain.
.PP
Multi-line comments are supported, but lines that resemble issue
metadata trailers (e.g., lines starting with
.IR "State:" ", " "Labels:" ", " "Priority:" )
are rejected to prevent accidental corruption of issue metadata.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fI<text>\fR
Comment text (required).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a comment:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue comment a1b2c3d -m "Fixed in commit abc1234"
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-show (1),
.BR git\-issue\-state (1)
